Attention ALL remote and in-person learners:

Just a friendly reminder that the following exams are required by October 15, 2020:
Physicals for grades Kindergarten, 6th, and 9th
Vision for Kindergarten
Immunizations for Kindergarten, 6th, and second Meningococcal vaccine for 12th.

Dental exams are required by May 15, 2021 for grades K, 2, 6, and 9.

Thank you for your help in completing the required exams and turning in the documentation as soon as possible.

Again, the PEF thanks you all for your generous support!

post_text:
It's FUNDRAISER time!! We know that this year is different, but we are still counting on all Washington and Lincoln students to help us raise much-needed funds for our elementary schools. As always, this will be our ONLY fundraiser for the year. Due to the times, we are offering two ways to offer support:

1. Mrs. Fields frozen catalog (collect orders AND money and turn both into the school)
-These items will be delivered to the school.

2. Ready Set Fund online sales and donations (NOTHING to collect/turn in)
-These items will be mailed directly to the customer. Here is the website:

www.readysetfund.com/panapto

Packets were sent home today with in-person learners, and remote learners will receive theirs at the next pickup date. Orders are due September 9. Please review the note and prize sheet included in the packet for other important information. THANK YOU!!

post_text:
REMINDER of Health Requirements for the 2020-2021 School Year:

Kindergarten--Immunizations, Physical, Dental, & Eye exams
2nd Grade--Dental exam
6th Grade--Immunizations, Physical, and Dental exams
Freshmen--Immunizations, Physical, and Dental exams
Seniors--Second Meningococcal conjugate vaccine

Immunizations, physicals, and eye exams must be completed by October 15th, 2020.

Dental exams must be completed by May 15th, 2021.

According to the IDPH and ISBE, there will be no extensions to these deadlines due to Covid-19.

Registration begins on Wed. July 22. Please make the time to get online and register soon....
ps- teacher names are NOT on the registration paperwork, they will be released once we know the number of students returning to in-person and the number for remote instruction at each grade level. This will help me create balanced class lists based on those numbers so we can best meet the needs of everyone.
pps- The district plan for the return to school was released on July 21 and each individual school
specific plan (based on that district plan) will be released on July 31. The specifics will be based on the most up to date guidance available. Thank you for your patience with this process.......
I can't wait to see you all again-- and please call if you have questions or need assistance!
